The **capital raising side** of the market. 
Let’s explain it with a simple story.

---

# Story: Company Needs More Money

Your company **ABC Ltd.** already did an IPO.

Now business is growing and they need:

* New factory 🏭
* Expansion 🌍

👉 They need more money again.

---

# Option: Issue More Shares

Instead of taking a loan, company says:

> “Let’s sell more shares to raise money”

This is called:

* **FPO (Follow-on Public Offering)**
* **Rights Issue**

---

# 1. FPO (Follow-on Public Offering)

## Story

ABC Ltd. share price in market = ₹500

Company announces:

> “We will sell new shares at ₹480”

---

## What happens?

* Public can buy new shares
* Company gets money

---

### Example

* 1 lakh new shares @ ₹480
    Company gets ₹4.8 crore

---

## Why price is lower than market?

To attract buyers quickly

---

## Who can buy?

* Anyone (public, institutions)

---

# 2. Rights Issue

This is more interesting 

---

## Story

Company says ONLY to existing shareholders:

> “You already own shares, so you get priority to buy more”

---

### Example

You own 100 shares

Company offers:

> “Buy 1 new share for every 2 shares you own at ₹300”

---

## What happens?

* You can buy 50 new shares @ ₹300
* Market price may be ₹500

👉 You get discount

---

## Why company does this?

* Reward loyal investors
* Raise money faster
* Avoid dilution complaints

---

# Key Difference

| Feature     | FPO             | Rights Issue           |
| ----------- | --------------- | ---------------------- |
| Who can buy | Public          | Existing shareholders  |
| Price       | Slight discount | Bigger discount        |
| Purpose     | Raise capital   | Raise capital + reward |

---

# 📉 Important Concept: Dilution

When company issues new shares:

👉 Total shares increase

---

## Example

Before:

* 100 shares total
* You own 10 → 10%

After issuing 100 more:

* Total = 200 shares
* You still have 10 → 5%

👉 Your ownership reduces

---

## This is called:

> **Dilution**

---

# Why Rights Issue Helps

You can buy more shares to:
    Maintain your ownership %

---

# 📊 Connection to Trading System

When FPO / Rights announced:

* Price may drop (more supply)
* Volume increases (more activity)

Your system handles:

* New orders
* Price adjustments

---

# Final Intuition

## FPO

> Company raises money from public again

## Rights Issue

> Company raises money from existing investors

---

# One-Line Memory

> “Company prints new shares to raise money — FPO for public, Rights for existing shareholders.”

